{
  "text": "Rivers are the chief carriers of dissolved and particulate matter from land to sea (e.g., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Damming on river alters its hydrological condition, material cycle and then transforms aquatic ecosystem from riverine type to limnological type (e.g., [CITATION_3] . Reservoirs created by dams are complex and dynamic ecosystems and it is important to understand how these ecosystems operate and respond to change for an efficient management [CITATION_4] . Picophytoplankton is an important component in freshwater ecosystem [CITATION_5] . They respond swiftly to environmental conditions and can be effectively used as early indicators of ecosystem change (e.g., [CITATION_6] . Nowadays, few studies have conducted with picophytoplankton in the cascade reservoirs (e.g., [CITATION_7] .",
